data.text:
Nicaragua has an area of 130,373.4 Km2. It is the center of the Central American isthmus. It has by Capital the city of managua.

As shown the map of Nicaragua is divided into 15 departments and 2 Autonomous Regions divided as follows:

Pacific Area:

Chinandega

Leon

Managua

Masaya

Carazo

Granada

Rivas

Central Area:

Nueva Segovia

Madriz

Estelí

Matagalpa

Boaco

Chontales

Rio San Juan

Jinotega

Atlantic Area:
